Selectors are not properties. They are patterns used to select HTML elements.

# CSS Selectors

## 1. Universal Selector
- `*`

## 2. Element (Type) Selector
- `h1`
- `p`
- `div`
- `span`

## 3. Class Selector
- `.classname`

## 4. ID Selector
- `#idname`

## 5. Grouping Selector
- `h1, p, div`

## 6. Descendant Selector
- `div p`

## 7. Child Selector
- `div > p`

## 8. Adjacent Sibling Selector
- `h1 + p`

## 9. General Sibling Selector
- `h1 ~ p`

## 10. Attribute Selectors
- `[attribute]`
- `[attribute="value"]`
- `[attribute~="value"]`
- `[attribute|="value"]`
- `[attribute^="value"]`
- `[attribute$="value"]`
- `[attribute*="value"]`

## 11. Pseudo-Class Selectors
- `:hover`
- `:active`
- `:focus`
- `:visited`
- `:link`
- `:checked`
- `:disabled`
- `:enabled`
- `:first-child`
- `:last-child`
- `:nth-child()`
- `:nth-of-type()`
- `:not()`
- `:empty`
- `:root`

## 12. Pseudo-Element Selectors
- `::before`
- `::after`
- `::first-letter`
- `::first-line`
- `::selection`
- `::placeholder`
- `::marker`

## Most Important Selectors

- `*` → Universal Selector
- `h1` → Element Selector
- `.class` → Class Selector
- `#id` → ID Selector
- `div p` → Descendant Selector
- `div > p` → Child Selector
- `:hover` → Hover State
- `:focus` → Focus State
- `:nth-child()` → Select Specific Child
- `::before` → Insert Content Before Element
- `::after` → Insert Content After Element
